4518
4519void ASTRecordWriter::AddAttr(const Attr *A) {
4520 auto &Record = *this;
4521 if (!A)
4522 return Record.push_back(0);
4523 Record.push_back(A->getKind() + 1); // FIXME: stable encoding, target attrs
4524 Record.AddSourceRange(A->getRange());
4525
4526#include "clang/Serialization/AttrPCHWrite.inc"
4527}
4528
4529/// Emit the list of attributes to the specified record.
4530void ASTRecordWriter::AddAttributes(ArrayRef<const Attr *> Attrs) {
4531 push_back(Attrs.size());
4532 for (const auto *A : Attrs)
4533 AddAttr(A);
4534}
4535
4536void ASTWriter::AddToken(const Token &Tok, RecordDataImpl &Record) {
4537 AddSourceLocation(Tok.getLocation(), Record);
4538 Record.push_back(Tok.getLength());
4539
4540 // FIXME: When reading literal tokens, reconstruct the literal pointer
4541 // if it is needed.
4542 AddIdentifierRef(Tok.getIdentifierInfo(), Record);
4543 // FIXME: Should translate token kind to a stable encoding.
4544 Record.push_back(Tok.getKind());
4545 // FIXME: Should translate token flags to a stable encoding.
4546 Record.push_back(Tok.getFlags());
4547}
4548
4549void ASTWriter::AddString(StringRef Str, RecordDataImpl &Record) {
4550 Record.push_back(Str.size());
4551 Record.insert(Record.end(), Str.begin(), Str.end());
4552}
4553
4554bool ASTWriter::PreparePathForOutput(SmallVectorImpl<char> &Path) {
4555 assert(Context && "should have context when outputting path");
4556
4557 bool Changed =
4558 cleanPathForOutput(Context->getSourceManager().getFileManager(), Path);
4559
4560 // Remove a prefix to make the path relative, if relevant.
4561 const char *PathBegin = Path.data();
4562 const char *PathPtr =
4563 adjustFilenameForRelocatableAST(PathBegin, BaseDirectory);
4564 if (PathPtr != PathBegin) {
4565 Path.erase(Path.begin(), Path.begin() + (PathPtr - PathBegin));
4566 Changed = true;
4567 }
4568
4569 return Changed;
4570}
4571
4572void ASTWriter::AddPath(StringRef Path, RecordDataImpl &Record) {
4573 SmallString<128> FilePath(Path);
4574 PreparePathForOutput(FilePath);
4575 AddString(FilePath, Record);
4576}
4577
4578void ASTWriter::EmitRecordWithPath(unsigned Abbrev, RecordDataRef Record,
4579 StringRef Path) {
4580 SmallString<128> FilePath(Path);
4581 PreparePathForOutput(FilePath);
4582 Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(Abbrev, Record, FilePath);
4583}
4584
4585void ASTWriter::AddVersionTuple(const VersionTuple &Version,
4586 RecordDataImpl &Record) {
4587 Record.push_back(Version.getMajor());
4588 if (Optional<unsigned> Minor = Version.getMinor())
4589 Record.push_back(*Minor + 1);
4590 else
4591 Record.push_back(0);
4592 if (Optional<unsigned> Subminor = Version.getSubminor())
4593 Record.push_back(*Subminor + 1);
4594 else
4595 Record.push_back(0);
4596}
4597
4598/// Note that the identifier II occurs at the given offset
4599/// within the identifier table.
4600void ASTWriter::SetIdentifierOffset(const IdentifierInfo *II, uint32_t Offset) {
4601 IdentID ID = IdentifierIDs[II];
4602 // Only store offsets new to this AST file. Other identifier names are looked
4603 // up earlier in the chain and thus don't need an offset.
4604 if (ID >= FirstIdentID)
4605 IdentifierOffsets[ID - FirstIdentID] = Offset;
4606}
4607
4608/// Note that the selector Sel occurs at the given offset
4609/// within the method pool/selector table.
4610void ASTWriter::SetSelectorOffset(Selector Sel, uint32_t Offset) {
4611 unsigned ID = SelectorIDs[Sel];
4612 assert(ID && "Unknown selector");
4613 // Don't record offsets for selectors that are also available in a different
4614 // file.
4615 if (ID < FirstSelectorID)
4616 return;
4617 SelectorOffsets[ID - FirstSelectorID] = Offset;
4618}

4620ASTWriter::ASTWriter(llvm::BitstreamWriter &Stream,
4621 SmallVectorImpl<char> &Buffer,
4622 InMemoryModuleCache &ModuleCache,
4623 ArrayRef<std::shared_ptr<ModuleFileExtension>> Extensions,
4624 bool IncludeTimestamps)
4625 : Stream(Stream), Buffer(Buffer), ModuleCache(ModuleCache),
4626 IncludeTimestamps(IncludeTimestamps) {
4627 for (const auto &Ext : Extensions) {
4628 if (auto Writer = Ext->createExtensionWriter(*this))
4629 ModuleFileExtensionWriters.push_back(std::move(Writer));
4630 }
4631}
4632
4633ASTWriter::~ASTWriter() {
4634 llvm::DeleteContainerSeconds(FileDeclIDs);
4635}
4636
4637const LangOptions &ASTWriter::getLangOpts() const {
4638 assert(WritingAST && "can't determine lang opts when not writing AST");
4639 return Context->getLangOpts();
4640}
4641
4642time_t ASTWriter::getTimestampForOutput(const FileEntry *E) const {
4643 return IncludeTimestamps ? E->getModificationTime() : 0;
4644}
4645
4646ASTFileSignature ASTWriter::WriteAST(Sema &SemaRef,
4647 const std::string &OutputFile,
4648 Module *WritingModule, StringRef isysroot,
4649 bool hasErrors,
4650 bool ShouldCacheASTInMemory) {
4651 WritingAST = true;
4652
4653 ASTHasCompilerErrors = hasErrors;
4654
4655 // Emit the file header.
4656 Stream.Emit((unsigned)'C', 8);
4657 Stream.Emit((unsigned)'P', 8);
4658 Stream.Emit((unsigned)'C', 8);
4659 Stream.Emit((unsigned)'H', 8);
4660
4661 WriteBlockInfoBlock();
4662
4663 Context = &SemaRef.Context;
4664 PP = &SemaRef.PP;
4665 this->WritingModule = WritingModule;
4666 ASTFileSignature Signature =
4667 WriteASTCore(SemaRef, isysroot, OutputFile, WritingModule);
4668 Context = nullptr;
4669 PP = nullptr;
4670 this->WritingModule = nullptr;
4671 this->BaseDirectory.clear();
4672
4673 WritingAST = false;
4674 if (ShouldCacheASTInMemory) {
4675 // Construct MemoryBuffer and update buffer manager.
4676 ModuleCache.addBuiltPCM(OutputFile,
4677 llvm::MemoryBuffer::getMemBufferCopy(
4678 StringRef(Buffer.begin(), Buffer.size())));
4679 }
4680 return Signature;
4681}
4682
4683template<typename Vector>
4684static void AddLazyVectorDecls(ASTWriter &Writer, Vector &Vec,
4685 ASTWriter::RecordData &Record) {
4686 for (typename Vector::iterator I = Vec.begin(nullptr, true), E = Vec.end();
4687 I != E; ++I) {
4688 Writer.AddDeclRef(*I, Record);
4689 }
4690}
4691
4692ASTFileSignature ASTWriter::WriteASTCore(Sema &SemaRef, StringRef isysroot,
4693 const std::string &OutputFile,
4694 Module *WritingModule) {
4695 using namespace llvm;
4696
4697 bool isModule = WritingModule != nullptr;
4698
4699 // Make sure that the AST reader knows to finalize itself.
4700 if (Chain)
4701 Chain->finalizeForWriting();
4702
4703 ASTContext &Context = SemaRef.Context;
4704 Preprocessor &PP = SemaRef.PP;
4705
4706 // Set up predefined declaration IDs.
4707 auto RegisterPredefDecl = [&] (Decl *D, PredefinedDeclIDs ID) {
4708 if (D) {
4709 assert(D->isCanonicalDecl() && "predefined decl is not canonical");
4710 DeclIDs[D] = ID;
4711 }
4712 };
4713 RegisterPredefDecl(Context.getTranslationUnitDecl(),
4714 PREDEF_DECL_TRANSLATION_UNIT_ID);
4715 RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ObjCIdDecl, PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_ID_ID);
4716 RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ObjCSelDecl, PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_SEL_ID);
4717 RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ObjCClassDecl, PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_CLASS_ID);
4718 RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ObjCProtocolClassDecl,
4719 PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_PROTOCOL_ID);
4720 RegisterPredefDecl(Context.Int128Decl, PREDEF_DECL_INT_128_ID);
4721 RegisterPredefDecl(Context.UInt128Decl, PREDEF_DECL_UNSIGNED_INT_128_ID);
4722 RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ObjCInstanceTypeDecl,
4723 PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_INSTANCETYPE_ID);
4724 RegisterPredefDecl(Context.BuiltinVaListDecl, PREDEF_DECL_BUILTIN_VA_LIST_ID);
4725 RegisterPredefDecl(Context.VaListTagDecl, PREDEF_DECL_VA_LIST_TAG);
4726 RegisterPredefDecl(Context.BuiltinMSVaListDecl,
4727 PREDEF_DECL_BUILTIN_MS_VA_LIST_ID);
4728 RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ExternCContext, PREDEF_DECL_EXTERN_C_CONTEXT_ID);
4729 RegisterPredefDecl(Context.MakeIntegerSeqDecl,
4730 PREDEF_DECL_MAKE_INTEGER_SEQ_ID);
4731 RegisterPredefDecl(Context.CFConstantStringTypeDecl,
4732 PREDEF_DECL_CF_CONSTANT_STRING_ID);
4733 RegisterPredefDecl(Context.CFConstantStringTagDecl,
4734 PREDEF_DECL_CF_CONSTANT_STRING_TAG_ID);
4735 RegisterPredefDecl(Context.TypePackElementDecl,
4736 PREDEF_DECL_TYPE_PACK_ELEMENT_ID);
4737
4738 // Build a record containing all of the tentative definitions in this file, in
4739 // TentativeDefinitions order. Generally, this record will be empty for
4740 // headers.
4741 RecordData TentativeDefinitions;
4742 AddLazyVectorDecls(*this, SemaRef.TentativeDefinitions, TentativeDefinitions);
4743
4744 // Build a record containing all of the file scoped decls in this file.
4745 RecordData UnusedFileScopedDecls;
4746 if (!isModule)
4747 AddLazyVectorDecls(*this, SemaRef.UnusedFileScopedDecls,
4748 UnusedFileScopedDecls);
4749
4750 // Build a record containing all of the delegating constructors we still need
4751 // to resolve.
4752 RecordData DelegatingCtorDecls;
4753 if (!isModule)
4754 AddLazyVectorDecls(*this, SemaRef.DelegatingCtorDecls, DelegatingCtorDecls);
4755
4756 // Write the set of weak, undeclared identifiers. We always write the
4757 // entire table, since later PCH files in a PCH chain are only interested in
4758 // the results at the end of the chain.
4759 RecordData WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers;
4760 for (auto &WeakUndeclaredIdentifier : SemaRef.WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers) {
4761 IdentifierInfo *II = WeakUndeclaredIdentifier.first;
4762 WeakInfo &WI = WeakUndeclaredIdentifier.second;
4763 AddIdentifierRef(II, WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers);
4764 AddIdentifierRef(WI.getAlias(), WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers);
4765 AddSourceLocation(WI.getLocation(), WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers);
4766 WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers.push_back(WI.getUsed());
4767 }
4768
4769 // Build a record containing all of the ext_vector declarations.
4770 RecordData ExtVectorDecls;
4771 AddLazyVectorDecls(*this, SemaRef.ExtVectorDecls, ExtVectorDecls);
4772
4773 // Build a record containing all of the VTable uses information.
4774 RecordData VTableUses;
4775 if (!SemaRef.VTableUses.empty()) {
4776 for (unsigned I = 0, N = SemaRef.VTableUses.size(); I != N; ++I) {
4777 AddDeclRef(SemaRef.VTableUses[I].first, VTableUses);
4778 AddSourceLocation(SemaRef.VTableUses[I].second, VTableUses);
4779 VTableUses.push_back(SemaRef.VTablesUsed[SemaRef.VTableUses[I].first]);
4780 }
4781 }
4782
4783 // Build a record containing all of the UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates.
4784 RecordData UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates;
4785 for (const TypedefNameDecl *TD : SemaRef.UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates)
4786 AddDeclRef(TD, UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates);
4787
4788 // Build a record containing all of pending implicit instantiations.
4789 RecordData PendingInstantiations;
4790 for (const auto &I : SemaRef.PendingInstantiations) {
4791 AddDeclRef(I.first, PendingInstantiations);
4792 AddSourceLocation(I.second, PendingInstantiations);
4793 }
4794 assert(SemaRef.PendingLocalImplicitInstantiations.empty() &&
4795 "There are local ones at end of translation unit!");
4796
4797 // Build a record containing some declaration references.
4798 RecordData SemaDeclRefs;
4799 if (SemaRef.StdNamespace || SemaRef.StdBadAlloc || SemaRef.StdAlignValT) {
4800 AddDeclRef(SemaRef.getStdNamespace(), SemaDeclRefs);
4801 AddDeclRef(SemaRef.getStdBadAlloc(), SemaDeclRefs);
4802 AddDeclRef(SemaRef.getStdAlignValT(), SemaDeclRefs);
4803 }
4804
4805 RecordData CUDASpecialDeclRefs;
4806 if (Context.getcudaConfigureCallDecl()) {
4807 AddDeclRef(Context.getcudaConfigureCallDecl(), CUDASpecialDeclRefs);
4808 }
4809
4810 // Build a record containing all of the known namespaces.
4811 RecordData KnownNamespaces;
4812 for (const auto &I : SemaRef.KnownNamespaces) {
4813 if (!I.second)
4814 AddDeclRef(I.first, KnownNamespaces);
4815 }
4816
4817 // Build a record of all used, undefined objects that require definitions.
4818 RecordData UndefinedButUsed;
4819
4820 SmallVector<std::pair<NamedDecl *, SourceLocation>, 16> Undefined;
4821 SemaRef.getUndefinedButUsed(Undefined);
4822 for (const auto &I : Undefined) {
4823 AddDeclRef(I.first, UndefinedButUsed);
4824 AddSourceLocation(I.second, UndefinedButUsed);
4825 }
4826
4827 // Build a record containing all delete-expressions that we would like to
4828 // analyze later in AST.
4829 RecordData DeleteExprsToAnalyze;
4830
4831 if (!isModule) {
4832 for (const auto &DeleteExprsInfo :
4833 SemaRef.getMismatchingDeleteExpressions()) {
4834 AddDeclRef(DeleteExprsInfo.first, DeleteExprsToAnalyze);
4835 DeleteExprsToAnalyze.push_back(DeleteExprsInfo.second.size());
4836 for (const auto &DeleteLoc : DeleteExprsInfo.second) {
4837 AddSourceLocation(DeleteLoc.first, DeleteExprsToAnalyze);
4838 DeleteExprsToAnalyze.push_back(DeleteLoc.second);
4839 }
4840 }
4841 }
4842
4843 // Write the control block
4844 WriteControlBlock(PP, Context, isysroot, OutputFile);
4845
4846 // Write the remaining AST contents.
4847 Stream.EnterSubblock(AST_BLOCK_ID, 5);
4848
4849 // This is so that older clang versions, before the introduction
4850 // of the control block, can read and reject the newer PCH format.
4851 {
4852 RecordData Record = {VERSION_MAJOR};
4853 Stream.EmitRecord(METADATA_OLD_FORMAT, Record);
4854 }
4855
4856 // Create a lexical update block containing all of the declarations in the
4857 // translation unit that do not come from other AST files.
4858 const TranslationUnitDecl *TU = Context.getTranslationUnitDecl();
4859 SmallVector<uint32_t, 128> NewGlobalKindDeclPairs;
4860 for (const auto *D : TU->noload_decls()) {
4861 if (!D->isFromASTFile()) {
4862 NewGlobalKindDeclPairs.push_back(D->getKind());
4863 NewGlobalKindDeclPairs.push_back(GetDeclRef(D));
4864 }
4865 }
4866
4867 auto Abv = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
4868 Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(TU_UPDATE_LEXICAL));
4869 Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
4870 unsigned TuUpdateLexicalAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abv));
4871 {
4872 RecordData::value_type Record[] = {TU_UPDATE_LEXICAL};
4873 Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(TuUpdateLexicalAbbrev, Record,
4874 bytes(NewGlobalKindDeclPairs));
4875 }
4876
4877 // And a visible updates block for the translation unit.
4878 Abv = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
4879 Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(UPDATE_VISIBLE));
4880 Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6));
4881 Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
4882 UpdateVisibleAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abv));
4883 WriteDeclContextVisibleUpdate(TU);
4884
4885 // If we have any extern "C" names, write out a visible update for them.
4886 if (Context.ExternCContext)
4887 WriteDeclContextVisibleUpdate(Context.ExternCContext);
4888
4889 // If the translation unit has an anonymous namespace, and we don't already
4890 // have an update block for it, write it as an update block.
4891 // FIXME: Why do we not do this if there's already an update block?
4892 if (NamespaceDecl *NS = TU->getAnonymousNamespace()) {
4893 ASTWriter::UpdateRecord &Record = DeclUpdates[TU];
4894 if (Record.empty())
4895 Record.push_back(DeclUpdate(UPD_CXX_ADDED_ANONYMOUS_NAMESPACE, NS));
4896 }
4897
4898 // Add update records for all mangling numbers and static local numbers.
4899 // These aren't really update records, but this is a convenient way of
4900 // tagging this rare extra data onto the declarations.
4901 for (const auto &Number : Context.MangleNumbers)
4902 if (!Number.first->isFromASTFile())
4903 DeclUpdates[Number.first].push_back(DeclUpdate(UPD_MANGLING_NUMBER,
4904 Number.second));
4905 for (const auto &Number : Context.StaticLocalNumbers)
4906 if (!Number.first->isFromASTFile())
4907 DeclUpdates[Number.first].push_back(DeclUpdate(UPD_STATIC_LOCAL_NUMBER,
4908 Number.second));
4909
4910 // Make sure visible decls, added to DeclContexts previously loaded from
4911 // an AST file, are registered for serialization. Likewise for template
4912 // specializations added to imported templates.
4913 for (const auto *I : DeclsToEmitEvenIfUnreferenced) {
4914 GetDeclRef(I);
4915 }
4916
4917 // Make sure all decls associated with an identifier are registered for
4918 // serialization, if we're storing decls with identifiers.
4919 if (!WritingModule || !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
4920 llvm::SmallVector<const IdentifierInfo*, 256> IIs;
4921 for (const auto &ID : PP.getIdentifierTable()) {
4922 const IdentifierInfo *II = ID.second;
4923 if (!Chain || !II->isFromAST() || II->hasChangedSinceDeserialization())
4924 IIs.push_back(II);
4925 }
4926 // Sort the identifiers to visit based on their name.
4927 llvm::sort(IIs, llvm::less_ptr<IdentifierInfo>());
4928 for (const IdentifierInfo *II : IIs) {
4929 for (IdentifierResolver::iterator D = SemaRef.IdResolver.begin(II),
4930 DEnd = SemaRef.IdResolver.end();
4931 D != DEnd; ++D) {
4932 GetDeclRef(*D);
4933 }
4934 }
4935 }
4936
4937 // For method pool in the module, if it contains an entry for a selector,
4938 // the entry should be complete, containing everything introduced by that
4939 // module and all modules it imports. It's possible that the entry is out of
4940 // date, so we need to pull in the new content here.
4941
4942 // It's possible that updateOutOfDateSelector can update SelectorIDs. To be
4943 // safe, we copy all selectors out.
4944 llvm::SmallVector<Selector, 256> AllSelectors;
4945 for (auto &SelectorAndID : SelectorIDs)
4946 AllSelectors.push_back(SelectorAndID.first);
4947 for (auto &Selector : AllSelectors)
4948 SemaRef.updateOutOfDateSelector(Selector);
4949
4950 // Form the record of special types.
4951 RecordData SpecialTypes;
4952 AddTypeRef(Context.getRawCFConstantStringType(), SpecialTypes);
4953 AddTypeRef(Context.getFILEType(), SpecialTypes);
4954 AddTypeRef(Context.getjmp_bufType(), SpecialTypes);
4955 AddTypeRef(Context.getsigjmp_bufType(), SpecialTypes);
4956 AddTypeRef(Context.ObjCIdRedefinitionType, SpecialTypes);
4957 AddTypeRef(Context.ObjCClassRedefinitionType, SpecialTypes);
4958 AddTypeRef(Context.ObjCSelRedefinitionType, SpecialTypes);
4959 AddTypeRef(Context.getucontext_tType(), SpecialTypes);
4960 AddTypeRef(Context.getpthread_tType(), SpecialTypes);
4961 AddTypeRef(Context.getpthread_attr_tType(), SpecialTypes);
4962
4963 if (Chain) {
4964 // Write the mapping information describing our module dependencies and how
4965 // each of those modules were mapped into our own offset/ID space, so that
4966 // the reader can build the appropriate mapping to its own offset/ID space.
4967 // The map consists solely of a blob with the following format:
4968 // *(module-kind:i8
4969 // module-name-len:i16 module-name:len*i8
4970 // source-location-offset:i32
4971 // identifier-id:i32
4972 // preprocessed-entity-id:i32
4973 // macro-definition-id:i32
4974 // submodule-id:i32
4975 // selector-id:i32
4976 // declaration-id:i32
4977 // c++-base-specifiers-id:i32
4978 // type-id:i32)
4979 //
4980 // module-kind is the ModuleKind enum value. If it is MK_PrebuiltModule or
4981 // MK_ExplicitModule, then the module-name is the module name. Otherwise,
4982 // it is the module file name.
4983 auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
4984 Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(MODULE_OFFSET_MAP));
4985 Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
4986 unsigned ModuleOffsetMapAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
4987 SmallString<2048> Buffer;
4988 {
4989 llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Buffer);
4990 for (ModuleFile &M : Chain->ModuleMgr) {
4991 using namespace llvm::support;
4992
4993 endian::Writer LE(Out, little);
4994 LE.write<uint8_t>(static_cast<uint8_t>(M.Kind));
4995 StringRef Name =
4996 M.Kind == MK_PrebuiltModule || M.Kind == MK_ExplicitModule
4997 ? M.ModuleName
4998 : M.FileName;
4999 LE.write<uint16_t>(Name.size());
5000 Out.write(Name.data(), Name.size());
5001
5002 // Note: if a base ID was uint max, it would not be possible to load
5003 // another module after it or have more than one entity inside it.
5004 uint32_t None = std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max();
5005
5006 auto writeBaseIDOrNone = [&](uint32_t BaseID, bool ShouldWrite) {
5007 assert(BaseID < std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max() && "base id too high");
5008 if (ShouldWrite)
5009 LE.write<uint32_t>(BaseID);
5010 else
5011 LE.write<uint32_t>(None);
5012 };
5013
5014 // These values should be unique within a chain, since they will be read
5015 // as keys into ContinuousRangeMaps.
5016 writeBaseIDOrNone(M.SLocEntryBaseOffset, M.LocalNumSLocEntries);
5017 writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseIdentifierID, M.LocalNumIdentifiers);
5018 writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseMacroID, M.LocalNumMacros);
5019 writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BasePreprocessedEntityID,
5020 M.NumPreprocessedEntities);
5021 writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseSubmoduleID, M.LocalNumSubmodules);
5022 writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseSelectorID, M.LocalNumSelectors);
5023 writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseDeclID, M.LocalNumDecls);
5024 writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseTypeIndex, M.LocalNumTypes);
5025 }
5026 }
5027 RecordData::value_type Record[] = {MODULE_OFFSET_MAP};
5028 Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(ModuleOffsetMapAbbrev, Record,
5029 Buffer.data(), Buffer.size());
5030 }
5031
5032 RecordData DeclUpdatesOffsetsRecord;
5033
5034 // Keep writing types, declarations, and declaration update records
5035 // until we've emitted all of them.
5036 Stream.EnterSubblock(DECLTYPES_BLOCK_ID, /*bits for abbreviations*/5);
5037 WriteTypeAbbrevs();
5038 WriteDeclAbbrevs();
5039 do {
5040 WriteDeclUpdatesBlocks(DeclUpdatesOffsetsRecord);
5041 while (!DeclTypesToEmit.empty()) {
5042 DeclOrType DOT = DeclTypesToEmit.front();
5043 DeclTypesToEmit.pop();
5044 if (DOT.isType())
5045 WriteType(DOT.getType());
5046 else
5047 WriteDecl(Context, DOT.getDecl());
5048 }
5049 } while (!DeclUpdates.empty());
5050 Stream.ExitBlock();
5051
5052 DoneWritingDeclsAndTypes = true;
5053
5054 // These things can only be done once we've written out decls and types.
5055 WriteTypeDeclOffsets();
5056 if (!DeclUpdatesOffsetsRecord.empty())
5057 Stream.EmitRecord(DECL_UPDATE_OFFSETS, DeclUpdatesOffsetsRecord);
5058 WriteFileDeclIDsMap();
5059 WriteSourceManagerBlock(Context.getSourceManager(), PP);
5060 WriteComments();
5061 WritePreprocessor(PP, isModule);
5062 WriteHeaderSearch(PP.getHeaderSearchInfo());
5063 WriteSelectors(SemaRef);
5064 WriteReferencedSelectorsPool(SemaRef);
5065 WriteLateParsedTemplates(SemaRef);
5066 WriteIdentifierTable(PP, SemaRef.IdResolver, isModule);
5067 WriteFPPragmaOptions(SemaRef.getFPOptions());
5068 WriteOpenCLExtensions(SemaRef);
5069 WriteOpenCLExtensionTypes(SemaRef);
5070 WriteCUDAPragmas(SemaRef);
5071
5072 // If we're emitting a module, write out the submodule information.
5073 if (WritingModule)
5074 WriteSubmodules(WritingModule);
5075
5076 // We need to have information about submodules to correctly deserialize
5077 // decls from OpenCLExtensionDecls block
5078 WriteOpenCLExtensionDecls(SemaRef);
5079
5080 Stream.EmitRecord(SPECIAL_TYPES, SpecialTypes);
5081
5082 // Write the record containing external, unnamed definitions.
5083 if (!EagerlyDeserializedDecls.empty())
5084 Stream.EmitRecord(EAGERLY_DESERIALIZED_DECLS, EagerlyDeserializedDecls);
5085
5086 if (!ModularCodegenDecls.empty())
5087 Stream.EmitRecord(MODULAR_CODEGEN_DECLS, ModularCodegenDecls);
5088
5089 // Write the record containing tentative definitions.
5090 if (!TentativeDefinitions.empty())
5091 Stream.EmitRecord(TENTATIVE_DEFINITIONS, TentativeDefinitions);
5092
5093 // Write the record containing unused file scoped decls.
5094 if (!UnusedFileScopedDecls.empty())
5095 Stream.EmitRecord(UNUSED_FILESCOPED_DECLS, UnusedFileScopedDecls);
5096
5097 // Write the record containing weak undeclared identifiers.
5098 if (!WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers.empty())
5099 Stream.EmitRecord(WEAK_UNDECLARED_IDENTIFIERS,
5100 WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers);
5101
5102 // Write the record containing ext_vector type names.
5103 if (!ExtVectorDecls.empty())
5104 Stream.EmitRecord(EXT_VECTOR_DECLS, ExtVectorDecls);
5105
5106 // Write the record containing VTable uses information.
5107 if (!VTableUses.empty())
5108 Stream.EmitRecord(VTABLE_USES, VTableUses);
5109
5110 // Write the record containing potentially unused local typedefs.
5111 if (!UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates.empty())
5112 Stream.EmitRecord(UNUSED_LOCAL_TYPEDEF_NAME_CANDIDATES,
5113 UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates);
5114
5115 // Write the record containing pending implicit instantiations.
5116 if (!PendingInstantiations.empty())
5117 Stream.EmitRecord(PENDING_IMPLICIT_INSTANTIATIONS, PendingInstantiations);
5118
5119 // Write the record containing declaration references of Sema.
5120 if (!SemaDeclRefs.empty())
5121 Stream.EmitRecord(SEMA_DECL_REFS, SemaDeclRefs);
5122
5123 // Write the record containing CUDA-specific declaration references.
5124 if (!CUDASpecialDeclRefs.empty())
5125 Stream.EmitRecord(CUDA_SPECIAL_DECL_REFS, CUDASpecialDeclRefs);
5126
5127 // Write the delegating constructors.
5128 if (!DelegatingCtorDecls.empty())
5129 Stream.EmitRecord(DELEGATING_CTORS, DelegatingCtorDecls);
5130
5131 // Write the known namespaces.
5132 if (!KnownNamespaces.empty())
5133 Stream.EmitRecord(KNOWN_NAMESPACES, KnownNamespaces);
5134
5135 // Write the undefined internal functions and variables, and inline functions.
5136 if (!UndefinedButUsed.empty())
5137 Stream.EmitRecord(UNDEFINED_BUT_USED, UndefinedButUsed);
5138
5139 if (!DeleteExprsToAnalyze.empty())
5140 Stream.EmitRecord(DELETE_EXPRS_TO_ANALYZE, DeleteExprsToAnalyze);
5141
5142 // Write the visible updates to DeclContexts.
5143 for (auto *DC : UpdatedDeclContexts)
5144 WriteDeclContextVisibleUpdate(DC);
5145
5146 if (!WritingModule) {
5147 // Write the submodules that were imported, if any.
5148 struct ModuleInfo {
5149 uint64_t ID;
5150 Module *M;
5151 ModuleInfo(uint64_t ID, Module *M) : ID(ID), M(M) {}
5152 };
5153 llvm::SmallVector<ModuleInfo, 64> Imports;
5154 for (const auto *I : Context.local_imports()) {
5155 assert(SubmoduleIDs.find(I->getImportedModule()) != SubmoduleIDs.end());
5156 Imports.push_back(ModuleInfo(SubmoduleIDs[I->getImportedModule()],
5157 I->getImportedModule()));
5158 }
5159
5160 if (!Imports.empty()) {
5161 auto Cmp = [](const ModuleInfo &A, const ModuleInfo &B) {
5162 return A.ID < B.ID;
5163 };
5164 auto Eq = [](const ModuleInfo &A, const ModuleInfo &B) {
5165 return A.ID == B.ID;
5166 };
5167
5168 // Sort and deduplicate module IDs.
5169 llvm::sort(Imports, Cmp);
5170 Imports.erase(std::unique(Imports.begin(), Imports.end(), Eq),
5171 Imports.end());
5172
5173 RecordData ImportedModules;
5174 for (const auto &Import : Imports) {
5175 ImportedModules.push_back(Import.ID);
5176 // FIXME: If the module has macros imported then later has declarations
5177 // imported, this location won't be the right one as a location for the
5178 // declaration imports.
5179 AddSourceLocation(PP.getModuleImportLoc(Import.M), ImportedModules);
5180 }
5181
5182 Stream.EmitRecord(IMPORTED_MODULES, ImportedModules);
5183 }
5184 }
5185
5186 WriteObjCCategories();
5187 if(!WritingModule) {
5188 WriteOptimizePragmaOptions(SemaRef);
5189 WriteMSStructPragmaOptions(SemaRef);
5190 WriteMSPointersToMembersPragmaOptions(SemaRef);
5191 }
5192 WritePackPragmaOptions(SemaRef);
5193
5194 // Some simple statistics
5195 RecordData::value_type Record[] = {
5196 NumStatements, NumMacros, NumLexicalDeclContexts, NumVisibleDeclContexts};
5197 Stream.EmitRecord(STATISTICS, Record);
5198 Stream.ExitBlock();
5199
5200 // Write the module file extension blocks.
5201 for (const auto &ExtWriter : ModuleFileExtensionWriters)
5202 WriteModuleFileExtension(SemaRef, *ExtWriter);
5203
5204 return writeUnhashedControlBlock(PP, Context);
5205}
5206
5207void ASTWriter::WriteDeclUpdatesBlocks(RecordDataImpl &OffsetsRecord) {
5208 if (DeclUpdates.empty())
5209 return;
5210
5211 DeclUpdateMap LocalUpdates;
5212 LocalUpdates.swap(DeclUpdates);
5213
5214 for (auto &DeclUpdate : LocalUpdates) {
5215 const Decl *D = DeclUpdate.first;
5216
5217 bool HasUpdatedBody = false;
5218 RecordData RecordData;
5219 ASTRecordWriter Record(*this, RecordData);
5220 for (auto &Update : DeclUpdate.second) {
5221 DeclUpdateKind Kind = (DeclUpdateKind)Update.getKind();
5222
5223 // An updated body is emitted last, so that the reader doesn't need
5224 // to skip over the lazy body to reach statements for other records.
5225 if (Kind == UPD_CXX_ADDED_FUNCTION_DEFINITION)
5226 HasUpdatedBody = true;
5227 else
5228 Record.push_back(Kind);
5229
5230 switch (Kind) {
5231 case UPD_CXX_ADDED_IMPLICIT_MEMBER:
5232 case UPD_CXX_ADDED_TEMPLATE_SPECIALIZATION:
5233 case UPD_CXX_ADDED_ANONYMOUS_NAMESPACE:
5234 assert(Update.getDecl() && "no decl to add?");
5235 Record.push_back(GetDeclRef(Update.getDecl()));
5236 break;
5237
5238 case UPD_CXX_ADDED_FUNCTION_DEFINITION:
5239 break;
5240
5241 case UPD_CXX_POINT_OF_INSTANTIATION:
5242 // FIXME: Do we need to also save the template specialization kind here?
5243 Record.AddSourceLocation(Update.getLoc());
5244 break;
5245
5246 case UPD_CXX_ADDED_VAR_DEFINITION: {
5247 const VarDecl *VD = cast<VarDecl>(D);
5248 Record.push_back(VD->isInline());
5249 Record.push_back(VD->isInlineSpecified());
5250 if (VD->getInit()) {
5251 Record.push_back(!VD->isInitKnownICE() ? 1
5252 : (VD->isInitICE() ? 3 : 2));
5253 Record.AddStmt(const_cast<Expr*>(VD->getInit()));
5254 } else {
5255 Record.push_back(0);
5256 }
5257 break;
5258 }
5259
5260 case UPD_CXX_INSTANTIATED_DEFAULT_ARGUMENT:
5261 Record.AddStmt(const_cast<Expr *>(
5262 cast<ParmVarDecl>(Update.getDecl())->getDefaultArg()));
5263 break;
5264
5265 case UPD_CXX_INSTANTIATED_DEFAULT_MEMBER_INITIALIZER:
5266 Record.AddStmt(
5267 cast<FieldDecl>(Update.getDecl())->getInClassInitializer());
5268 break;
5269
5270 case UPD_CXX_INSTANTIATED_CLASS_DEFINITION: {
5271 auto *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D);
5272 UpdatedDeclContexts.insert(RD->getPrimaryContext());
5273 Record.push_back(RD->isParamDestroyedInCallee());
5274 Record.push_back(RD->getArgPassingRestrictions());
5275 Record.AddCXXDefinitionData(RD);
5276 Record.AddOffset(WriteDeclContextLexicalBlock(
5277 *Context, const_cast<CXXRecordDecl *>(RD)));
5278
5279 // This state is sometimes updated by template instantiation, when we
5280 // switch from the specialization referring to the template declaration
5281 // to it referring to the template definition.
5282 if (auto *MSInfo = RD->getMemberSpecializationInfo()) {
5283 Record.push_back(MSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind());
5284 Record.AddSourceLocation(MSInfo->getPointOfInstantiation());
5285 } else {
5286 auto *Spec = cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD);
5287 Record.push_back(Spec->getTemplateSpecializationKind());
5288 Record.AddSourceLocation(Spec->getPointOfInstantiation());
5289
5290 // The instantiation might have been resolved to a partial
5291 // specialization. If so, record which one.
5292 auto From = Spec->getInstantiatedFrom();
5293 if (auto PartialSpec =
5294 From.dyn_cast<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl*>()) {
5295 Record.push_back(true);
5296 Record.AddDeclRef(PartialSpec);
5297 Record.AddTemplateArgumentList(
5298 &Spec->getTemplateInstantiationArgs());
5299 } else {
5300 Record.push_back(false);
5301 }
5302 }
5303 Record.push_back(RD->getTagKind());
5304 Record.AddSourceLocation(RD->getLocation());
5305 Record.AddSourceLocation(RD->getBeginLoc());
5306 Record.AddSourceRange(RD->getBraceRange());
5307
5308 // Instantiation may change attributes; write them all out afresh.
5309 Record.push_back(D->hasAttrs());
5310 if (D->hasAttrs())
5311 Record.AddAttributes(D->getAttrs());
5312
5313 // FIXME: Ensure we don't get here for explicit instantiations.
5314 break;
5315 }
5316
5317 case UPD_CXX_RESOLVED_DTOR_DELETE:
5318 Record.AddDeclRef(Update.getDecl());
5319 Record.AddStmt(cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(D)->getOperatorDeleteThisArg());
5320 break;
5321
5322 case UPD_CXX_RESOLVED_EXCEPTION_SPEC:
5323 addExceptionSpec(
5324 cast<FunctionDecl>(D)->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>(),
5325 Record);
5326 break;
5327
5328 case UPD_CXX_DEDUCED_RETURN_TYPE:
5329 Record.push_back(GetOrCreateTypeID(Update.getType()));
5330 break;
5331
5332 case UPD_DECL_MARKED_USED:
5333 break;
5334
5335 case UPD_MANGLING_NUMBER:
5336 case UPD_STATIC_LOCAL_NUMBER:
5337 Record.push_back(Update.getNumber());
5338 break;
5339
5340 case UPD_DECL_MARKED_OPENMP_THREADPRIVATE:
5341 Record.AddSourceRange(
5342 D->getAttr<OMPThreadPrivateDeclAttr>()->getRange());
5343 break;
5344
5345 case UPD_DECL_MARKED_OPENMP_ALLOCATE: {
5346 auto *A = D->getAttr<OMPAllocateDeclAttr>();
5347 Record.push_back(A->getAllocatorType());
5348 Record.AddStmt(A->getAllocator());
5349 Record.AddSourceRange(A->getRange());
5350 break;
5351 }
5352
5353 case UPD_DECL_MARKED_OPENMP_DECLARETARGET:
5354 Record.push_back(D->getAttr<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr>()->getMapType());
5355 Record.AddSourceRange(
5356 D->getAttr<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr>()->getRange());
5357 break;
5358
5359 case UPD_DECL_EXPORTED:
5360 Record.push_back(getSubmoduleID(Update.getModule()));
5361 break;
5362
5363 case UPD_ADDED_ATTR_TO_RECORD:
5364 Record.AddAttributes(llvm::makeArrayRef(Update.getAttr()));
5365 break;
5366 }
5367 }
5368
5369 if (HasUpdatedBody) {
5370 const auto *Def = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
5371 Record.push_back(UPD_CXX_ADDED_FUNCTION_DEFINITION);
5372 Record.push_back(Def->isInlined());
5373 Record.AddSourceLocation(Def->getInnerLocStart());
5374 Record.AddFunctionDefinition(Def);
5375 }
5376
5377 OffsetsRecord.push_back(GetDeclRef(D));
5378 OffsetsRecord.push_back(Record.Emit(DECL_UPDATES));
5379 }
5380}
5381
5382void ASTWriter::AddSourceLocation(SourceLocation Loc, RecordDataImpl &Record) {
5383 uint32_t Raw = Loc.getRawEncoding();
5384 Record.push_back((Raw << 1) | (Raw >> 31));
5385}
5386
5387void ASTWriter::AddSourceRange(SourceRange Range, RecordDataImpl &Record) {
5388 AddSourceLocation(Range.getBegin(), Record);
5389 AddSourceLocation(Range.getEnd(), Record);
5390}
5391
5392void ASTRecordWriter::AddAPInt(const llvm::APInt &Value) {
5393 Record->push_back(Value.getBitWidth());
5394 const uint64_t *Words = Value.getRawData();
5395 Record->append(Words, Words + Value.getNumWords());
5396}
5397
5398void ASTRecordWriter::AddAPSInt(const llvm::APSInt &Value) {
5399 Record->push_back(Value.isUnsigned());
5400 AddAPInt(Value);
5401}
5402
5403void ASTRecordWriter::AddAPFloat(const llvm::APFloat &Value) {
5404 AddAPInt(Value.bitcastToAPInt());
5405}
5406
5407void ASTWriter::AddIdentifierRef(const IdentifierInfo *II, RecordDataImpl &Record) {
5408 Record.push_back(getIdentifierRef(II));
5409}
5410
5411IdentID ASTWriter::getIdentifierRef(const IdentifierInfo *II) {
5412 if (!II)
5413 return 0;
5414
5415 IdentID &ID = IdentifierIDs[II];
5416 if (ID == 0)
5417 ID = NextIdentID++;
5418 return ID;
5419}
5420
5421MacroID ASTWriter::getMacroRef(MacroInfo *MI, const IdentifierInfo *Name) {
5422 // Don't emit builtin macros like __LINE__ to the AST file unless they
5423 // have been redefined by the header (in which case they are not
5424 // isBuiltinMacro).
5425 if (!MI || MI->isBuiltinMacro())
5426 return 0;
5427
5428 MacroID &ID = MacroIDs[MI];
5429 if (ID == 0) {
5430 ID = NextMacroID++;
5431 MacroInfoToEmitData Info = { Name, MI, ID };
5432 MacroInfosToEmit.push_back(Info);
5433 }
5434 return ID;
5435}
5436
5437MacroID ASTWriter::getMacroID(MacroInfo *MI) {
5438 if (!MI || MI->isBuiltinMacro())
5439 return 0;
5440
5441 assert(MacroIDs.find(MI) != MacroIDs.end() && "Macro not emitted!");
5442 return MacroIDs[MI];
5443}
5444
5445uint64_t ASTWriter::getMacroDirectivesOffset(const IdentifierInfo *Name) {
5446 return IdentMacroDirectivesOffsetMap.lookup(Name);
5447}
5448
5449void ASTRecordWriter::AddSelectorRef(const Selector SelRef) {
5450 Record->push_back(Writer->getSelectorRef(SelRef));
5451}
5452
5453SelectorID ASTWriter::getSelectorRef(Selector Sel) {
5454 if (Sel.getAsOpaquePtr() == nullptr) {
5455 return 0;
5456 }
5457
5458 SelectorID SID = SelectorIDs[Sel];
5459 if (SID == 0 && Chain) {
5460 // This might trigger a ReadSelector callback, which will set the ID for
5461 // this selector.
5462 Chain->LoadSelector(Sel);
5463 SID = SelectorIDs[Sel];
5464 }
5465 if (SID == 0) {
5466 SID = NextSelectorID++;
5467 SelectorIDs[Sel] = SID;
5468 }
5469 return SID;
5470}
5471
5472void ASTRecordWriter::AddCXXTemporary(const CXXTemporary *Temp) {
5473 AddDeclRef(Temp->getDestructor());
5474}
5475
5476void ASTRecordWriter::AddTemplateArgumentLocInfo(
5477 TemplateArgument::ArgKind Kind, const TemplateArgumentLocInfo &Arg) {
5478 switch (Kind) {
5479 case TemplateArgument::Expression:
5480 AddStmt(Arg.getAsExpr());
5481 break;
5482 case TemplateArgument::Type:
5483 AddTypeSourceInfo(Arg.getAsTypeSourceInfo());
5484 break;
5485 case TemplateArgument::Template:
5486 AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(Arg.getTemplateQualifierLoc());
5487 AddSourceLocation(Arg.getTemplateNameLoc());
5488 break;
5489 case TemplateArgument::TemplateExpansion:
5490 AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(Arg.getTemplateQualifierLoc());
5491 AddSourceLocation(Arg.getTemplateNameLoc());
5492 AddSourceLocation(Arg.getTemplateEllipsisLoc());
5493 break;
5494 case TemplateArgument::Null:
5495 case TemplateArgument::Integral:
5496 case TemplateArgument::Declaration:
5497 case TemplateArgument::NullPtr:
5498 case TemplateArgument::Pack:
5499 // FIXME: Is this right?
5500 break;
5501 }
5502}
5503
5504void ASTRecordWriter::AddTemplateArgumentLoc(const TemplateArgumentLoc &Arg) {
5505 AddTemplateArgument(Arg.getArgument());
5506
5507 if (Arg.getArgument().getKind() == TemplateArgument::Expression) {
5508 bool InfoHasSameExpr
5509 = Arg.getArgument().getAsExpr() == Arg.getLocInfo().getAsExpr();
5510 Record->push_back(InfoHasSameExpr);
5511 if (InfoHasSameExpr)
5512 return; // Avoid storing the same expr twice.
5513 }
5514 AddTemplateArgumentLocInfo(Arg.getArgument().getKind(), Arg.getLocInfo());
5515}
5516
5517void ASTRecordWriter::AddTypeSourceInfo(TypeSourceInfo *TInfo) {
5518 if (!TInfo) {
5519 AddTypeRef(QualType());
5520 return;
5521 }
5522
5523 AddTypeRef(TInfo->getType());
5524 AddTypeLoc(TInfo->getTypeLoc());
5525}
5526
5527void ASTRecordWriter::AddTypeLoc(TypeLoc TL) {
5528 TypeLocWriter TLW(*this);
5529 for (; !TL.isNull(); TL = TL.getNextTypeLoc())
5530 TLW.Visit(TL);
5531}
5532
5533void ASTWriter::AddTypeRef(QualType T, RecordDataImpl &Record) {
5534 Record.push_back(GetOrCreateTypeID(T));
5535}
5536
5537TypeID ASTWriter::GetOrCreateTypeID(QualType T) {
5538 assert(Context);
5539 return MakeTypeID(*Context, T, [&](QualType T) -> TypeIdx {
5540 if (T.isNull())
5541 return TypeIdx();
5542 assert(!T.getLocalFastQualifiers());
5543
5544 TypeIdx &Idx = TypeIdxs[T];
5545 if (Idx.getIndex() == 0) {
5546 if (DoneWritingDeclsAndTypes) {
5547 assert(0 && "New type seen after serializing all the types to emit!");
5548 return TypeIdx();
5549 }
5550
5551 // We haven't seen this type before. Assign it a new ID and put it
5552 // into the queue of types to emit.
5553 Idx = TypeIdx(NextTypeID++);
5554 DeclTypesToEmit.push(T);
5555 }
5556 return Idx;
5557 });
5558}
5559
5560TypeID ASTWriter::getTypeID(QualType T) const {
5561 assert(Context);
5562 return MakeTypeID(*Context, T, [&](QualType T) -> TypeIdx {
5563 if (T.isNull())
5564 return TypeIdx();
5565 assert(!T.getLocalFastQualifiers());
5566
5567 TypeIdxMap::const_iterator I = TypeIdxs.find(T);
5568 assert(I != TypeIdxs.end() && "Type not emitted!");
5569 return I->second;
5570 });
5571}
5572
5573void ASTWriter::AddDeclRef(const Decl *D, RecordDataImpl &Record) {
5574 Record.push_back(GetDeclRef(D));
5575}
5576
5577DeclID ASTWriter::GetDeclRef(const Decl *D) {
5578 assert(WritingAST && "Cannot request a declaration ID before AST writing");
5579
5580 if (!D) {
5581 return 0;
5582 }
5583
5584 // If D comes from an AST file, its declaration ID is already known and
5585 // fixed.
5586 if (D->isFromASTFile())
5587 return D->getGlobalID();
5588
5589 assert(!(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(D) & 0x01) && "Invalid decl pointer");
5590 DeclID &ID = DeclIDs[D];
5591 if (ID == 0) {
5592 if (DoneWritingDeclsAndTypes) {
5593 assert(0 && "New decl seen after serializing all the decls to emit!");
5594 return 0;
5595 }
5596
5597 // We haven't seen this declaration before. Give it a new ID and
5598 // enqueue it in the list of declarations to emit.
5599 ID = NextDeclID++;
5600 DeclTypesToEmit.push(const_cast<Decl *>(D));
5601 }
5602
5603 return ID;
5604}
5605
5606DeclID ASTWriter::getDeclID(const Decl *D) {
5607 if (!D)
5608 return 0;
5609
5610 // If D comes from an AST file, its declaration ID is already known and
5611 // fixed.
5612 if (D->isFromASTFile())
5613 return D->getGlobalID();
5614
5615 assert(DeclIDs.find(D) != DeclIDs.end() && "Declaration not emitted!");
5616 return DeclIDs[D];
5617}
5618
5619void ASTWriter::associateDeclWithFile(const Decl *D, DeclID ID) {
5620 assert(ID);
5621 assert(D);
5622
5623 SourceLocation Loc = D->getLocation();
5624 if (Loc.isInvalid())
5625 return;
5626
5627 // We only keep track of the file-level declarations of each file.
5628 if (!D->getLexicalDeclContext()->isFileContext())
5629 return;
5630 // FIXME: ParmVarDecls that are part of a function type of a parameter of
5631 // a function/objc method, should not have TU as lexical context.
5632 // TemplateTemplateParmDecls that are part of an alias template, should not
5633 // have TU as lexical context.
5634 if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(D) || isa<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(D))
5635 return;
5636
5637 SourceManager &SM = Context->getSourceManager();
5638 SourceLocation FileLoc = SM.getFileLoc(Loc);
5639 assert(SM.isLocalSourceLocation(FileLoc));
5640 FileID FID;
5641 unsigned Offset;
5642 std::tie(FID, Offset) = SM.getDecomposedLoc(FileLoc);
5643 if (FID.isInvalid())
5644 return;
5645 assert(SM.getSLocEntry(FID).isFile());
5646
5647 DeclIDInFileInfo *&Info = FileDeclIDs[FID];
5648 if (!Info)
5649 Info = new DeclIDInFileInfo();
5650
5651 std::pair<unsigned, serialization::DeclID> LocDecl(Offset, ID);
5652 LocDeclIDsTy &Decls = Info->DeclIDs;
5653
5654 if (Decls.empty() || Decls.back().first <= Offset) {
5655 Decls.push_back(LocDecl);
5656 return;
5657 }
5658
5659 LocDeclIDsTy::iterator I =
5660 std::upper_bound(Decls.begin(), Decls.end(), LocDecl, llvm::less_first());
5661
5662 Decls.insert(I, LocDecl);
5663}
5664
5665void ASTRecordWriter::AddDeclarationName(DeclarationName Name) {
5666 // FIXME: Emit a stable enum for NameKind. 0 = Identifier etc.
5667 Record->push_back(Name.getNameKind());
5668 switch (Name.getNameKind()) {
5669 case DeclarationName::Identifier:
5670 AddIdentifierRef(Name.getAsIdentifierInfo());
5671 break;
5672
5673 case DeclarationName::ObjCZeroArgSelector:
5674 case DeclarationName::ObjCOneArgSelector:
5675 case DeclarationName::ObjCMultiArgSelector:
5676 AddSelectorRef(Name.getObjCSelector());
5677 break;
5678
5679 case DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName:
5680 case DeclarationName::CXXDestructorName:
5681 case DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName:
5682 AddTypeRef(Name.getCXXNameType());
5683 break;
5684
5685 case DeclarationName::CXXDeductionGuideName:
5686 AddDeclRef(Name.getCXXDeductionGuideTemplate());
5687 break;
5688
5689 case DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName:
5690 Record->push_back(Name.getCXXOverloadedOperator());
5691 break;
5692
5693 case DeclarationName::CXXLiteralOperatorName:
5694 AddIdentifierRef(Name.getCXXLiteralIdentifier());
5695 break;
5696
5697 case DeclarationName::CXXUsingDirective:
5698 // No extra data to emit
5699 break;
5700 }
5701}
5702
5703unsigned ASTWriter::getAnonymousDeclarationNumber(const NamedDecl *D) {
5704 assert(needsAnonymousDeclarationNumber(D) &&
5705 "expected an anonymous declaration");
5706
5707 // Number the anonymous declarations within this context, if we've not
5708 // already done so.
5709 auto It = AnonymousDeclarationNumbers.find(D);
5710 if (It == AnonymousDeclarationNumbers.end()) {
5711 auto *DC = D->getLexicalDeclContext();
5712 numberAnonymousDeclsWithin(DC, [&](const NamedDecl *ND, unsigned Number) {
5713 AnonymousDeclarationNumbers[ND] = Number;
5714 });
5715
5716 It = AnonymousDeclarationNumbers.find(D);
5717 assert(It != AnonymousDeclarationNumbers.end() &&
5718 "declaration not found within its lexical context");
5719 }
5720
5721 return It->second;
5722}
5723
5724void ASTRecordWriter::AddDeclarationNameLoc(const DeclarationNameLoc &DNLoc,
5725 DeclarationName Name) {
5726 switch (Name.getNameKind()) {
5727 case DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName:
5728 case DeclarationName::CXXDestructorName:
5729 case DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName:
5730 AddTypeSourceInfo(DNLoc.NamedType.TInfo);
5731 break;
5732
5733 case DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName:
5734 AddSourceLocation(SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(
5735 DNLoc.CXXOperatorName.BeginOpNameLoc));
5736 AddSourceLocation(
5737 SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(DNLoc.CXXOperatorName.EndOpNameLoc));
5738 break;
5739
5740 case DeclarationName::CXXLiteralOperatorName:
5741 AddSourceLocation(SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(
5742 DNLoc.CXXLiteralOperatorName.OpNameLoc));
5743 break;
5744
5745 case DeclarationName::Identifier:
5746 case DeclarationName::ObjCZeroArgSelector:
5747 case DeclarationName::ObjCOneArgSelector:
5748 case DeclarationName::ObjCMultiArgSelector:
5749 case DeclarationName::CXXUsingDirective:
5750 case DeclarationName::CXXDeductionGuideName:
5751 break;
5752 }
5753}
5754
5755void ASTRecordWriter::AddDeclarationNameInfo(
5756 const DeclarationNameInfo &NameInfo) {
5757 AddDeclarationName(NameInfo.getName());
5758 AddSourceLocation(NameInfo.getLoc());
5759 AddDeclarationNameLoc(NameInfo.getInfo(), NameInfo.getName());
5760}
5761
5762void ASTRecordWriter::AddQualifierInfo(const QualifierInfo &Info) {
5763 AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(Info.QualifierLoc);
5764 Record->push_back(Info.NumTemplParamLists);
5765 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Info.NumTemplParamLists; i != e; ++i)
5766 AddTemplateParameterList(Info.TemplParamLists[i]);
5767}
5768
5769void ASTRecordWriter::AddNestedNameSpecifier(NestedNameSpecifier *NNS) {
5770 // Nested name specifiers usually aren't too long. I think that 8 would
5771 // typically accommodate the vast majority.
5772 SmallVector<NestedNameSpecifier *, 8> NestedNames;
5773
5774 // Push each of the NNS's onto a stack for serialization in reverse order.
5775 while (NNS) {
5776 NestedNames.push_back(NNS);
5777 NNS = NNS->getPrefix();
5778 }
5779
5780 Record->push_back(NestedNames.size());
5781 while(!NestedNames.empty()) {
5782 NNS = NestedNames.pop_back_val();
5783 NestedNameSpecifier::SpecifierKind Kind = NNS->getKind();
5784 Record->push_back(Kind);
5785 switch (Kind) {
5786 case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier:
5787 AddIdentifierRef(NNS->getAsIdentifier());
5788 break;
5789
5790 case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace:
5791 AddDeclRef(NNS->getAsNamespace());
5792 break;
5793
5794 case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias:
5795 AddDeclRef(NNS->getAsNamespaceAlias());
5796 break;
5797
5798 case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec:
5799 case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate:
5800 AddTypeRef(QualType(NNS->getAsType(), 0));
5801 Record->push_back(Kind == NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate);
5802 break;
5803
5804 case NestedNameSpecifier::Global:
5805 // Don't need to write an associated value.
5806 break;
5807
5808 case NestedNameSpecifier::Super:
5809 AddDeclRef(NNS->getAsRecordDecl());
5810 break;
5811 }
5812 }
5813}
5814
5815void ASTRecordWriter::AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(NestedNameSpecifierLoc NNS) {
5816 // Nested name specifiers usually aren't too long. I think that 8 would
5817 // typically accommodate the vast majority.
5818 SmallVector<NestedNameSpecifierLoc , 8> NestedNames;
5819
5820 // Push each of the nested-name-specifiers's onto a stack for
5821 // serialization in reverse order.
5822 while (NNS) {
5823 NestedNames.push_back(NNS);
5824 NNS = NNS.getPrefix();
5825 }
5826
5827 Record->push_back(NestedNames.size());
5828 while(!NestedNames.empty()) {
5829 NNS = NestedNames.pop_back_val();
5830 NestedNameSpecifier::SpecifierKind Kind
5831 = NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier()->getKind();
5832 Record->push_back(Kind);
5833 switch (Kind) {
5834 case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier:
5835 AddIdentifierRef(NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier()->getAsIdentifier());
5836 AddSourceRange(NNS.getLocalSourceRange());
5837 break;
5838
5839 case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace:
5840 AddDeclRef(NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier()->getAsNamespace());
5841 AddSourceRange(NNS.getLocalSourceRange());
5842 break;
5843
5844 case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias:
5845 AddDeclRef(NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier()->getAsNamespaceAlias());
5846 AddSourceRange(NNS.getLocalSourceRange());
5847 break;
5848
5849 case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec:
5850 case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate:
5851 Record->push_back(Kind == NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate);
5852 AddTypeRef(NNS.getTypeLoc().getType());
5853 AddTypeLoc(NNS.getTypeLoc());
5854 AddSourceLocation(NNS.getLocalSourceRange().getEnd());
5855 break;
5856
5857 case NestedNameSpecifier::Global:
5858 AddSourceLocation(NNS.getLocalSourceRange().getEnd());
5859 break;
5860
5861 case NestedNameSpecifier::Super:
5862 AddDeclRef(NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier()->getAsRecordDecl());
5863 AddSourceRange(NNS.getLocalSourceRange());
5864 break;
5865 }
5866 }
5867}
5868
5869void ASTRecordWriter::AddTemplateName(TemplateName Name) {
5870 TemplateName::NameKind Kind = Name.getKind();
5871 Record->push_back(Kind);
5872 switch (Kind) {
5873 case TemplateName::Template:
5874 AddDeclRef(Name.getAsTemplateDecl());
5875 break;
5876
5877 case TemplateName::OverloadedTemplate: {
5878 OverloadedTemplateStorage *OvT = Name.getAsOverloadedTemplate();
5879 Record->push_back(OvT->size());
5880 for (const auto &I : *OvT)
5881 AddDeclRef(I);
5882 break;
5883 }
5884
5885 case TemplateName::AssumedTemplate: {
5886 AssumedTemplateStorage *ADLT = Name.getAsAssumedTemplateName();
5887 AddDeclarationName(ADLT->getDeclName());
5888 break;
5889 }
5890
5891 case TemplateName::QualifiedTemplate: {
5892 QualifiedTemplateName *QualT = Name.getAsQualifiedTemplateName();
5893 AddNestedNameSpecifier(QualT->getQualifier());
5894 Record->push_back(QualT->hasTemplateKeyword());
5895 AddDeclRef(QualT->getTemplateDecl());
5896 break;
5897 }
5898
5899 case TemplateName::DependentTemplate: {
5900 DependentTemplateName *DepT = Name.getAsDependentTemplateName();
5901 AddNestedNameSpecifier(DepT->getQualifier());
5902 Record->push_back(DepT->isIdentifier());
5903 if (DepT->isIdentifier())
5904 AddIdentifierRef(DepT->getIdentifier());
5905 else
5906 Record->push_back(DepT->getOperator());
5907 break;
5908 }
5909
5910 case TemplateName::SubstTemplateTemplateParm: {
5911 SubstTemplateTemplateParmStorage *subst
5912 = Name.getAsSubstTemplateTemplateParm();
5913 AddDeclRef(subst->getParameter());
5914 AddTemplateName(subst->getReplacement());
5915 break;
5916 }
5917
5918 case TemplateName::SubstTemplateTemplateParmPack: {
5919 SubstTemplateTemplateParmPackStorage *SubstPack
5920 = Name.getAsSubstTemplateTemplateParmPack();
5921 AddDeclRef(SubstPack->getParameterPack());
5922 AddTemplateArgument(SubstPack->getArgumentPack());
5923 break;
5924 }
5925 }
5926}
5927
5928void ASTRecordWriter::AddTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &Arg) {
5929 Record->push_back(Arg.getKind());
5930 switch (Arg.getKind()) {
5931 case TemplateArgument::Null:
5932 break;
5933 case TemplateArgument::Type:
5934 AddTypeRef(Arg.getAsType());
5935 break;
5936 case TemplateArgument::Declaration:
5937 AddDeclRef(Arg.getAsDecl());
5938 AddTypeRef(Arg.getParamTypeForDecl());
5939 break;
5940 case TemplateArgument::NullPtr:
5941 AddTypeRef(Arg.getNullPtrType());
5942 break;
5943 case TemplateArgument::Integral:
5944 AddAPSInt(Arg.getAsIntegral());
5945 AddTypeRef(Arg.getIntegralType());
5946 break;
5947 case TemplateArgument::Template:
5948 AddTemplateName(Arg.getAsTemplateOrTemplatePattern());
5949 break;
5950 case TemplateArgument::TemplateExpansion:
5951 AddTemplateName(Arg.getAsTemplateOrTemplatePattern());
5952 if (Optional<unsigned> NumExpansions = Arg.getNumTemplateExpansions())
5953 Record->push_back(*NumExpansions + 1);
5954 else
5955 Record->push_back(0);
5956 break;
5957 case TemplateArgument::Expression:
5958 AddStmt(Arg.getAsExpr());
5959 break;
5960 case TemplateArgument::Pack:
5961 Record->push_back(Arg.pack_size());
5962 for (const auto &P : Arg.pack_elements())
5963 AddTemplateArgument(P);
5964 break;
5965 }
5966}
5967
5968void ASTRecordWriter::AddTemplateParameterList(
5969 const TemplateParameterList *TemplateParams) {
5970 assert(TemplateParams && "No TemplateParams!");
5971 AddSourceLocation(TemplateParams->getTemplateLoc());
5972 AddSourceLocation(TemplateParams->getLAngleLoc());
5973 AddSourceLocation(TemplateParams->getRAngleLoc());
5974 // TODO: Concepts
5975 Record->push_back(TemplateParams->size());
5976 for (const auto &P : *TemplateParams)
5977 AddDeclRef(P);
5978}
5979
5980/// Emit a template argument list.
5981void ASTRecordWriter::AddTemplateArgumentList(
5982 const TemplateArgumentList *TemplateArgs) {
5983 assert(TemplateArgs && "No TemplateArgs!");
5984 Record->push_back(TemplateArgs->size());
5985 for (int i = 0, e = TemplateArgs->size(); i != e; ++i)
5986 AddTemplateArgument(TemplateArgs->get(i));
5987}
5988
5989void ASTRecordWriter::AddASTTemplateArgumentListInfo(
5990 const ASTTemplateArgumentListInfo *ASTTemplArgList) {
5991 assert(ASTTemplArgList && "No ASTTemplArgList!");
5992 AddSourceLocation(ASTTemplArgList->LAngleLoc);
5993 AddSourceLocation(ASTTemplArgList->RAngleLoc);
5994 Record->push_back(ASTTemplArgList->NumTemplateArgs);
5995 const TemplateArgumentLoc *TemplArgs = ASTTemplArgList->getTemplateArgs();
5996 for (int i = 0, e = ASTTemplArgList->NumTemplateArgs; i != e; ++i)
5997 AddTemplateArgumentLoc(TemplArgs[i]);
5998}
5999
6000void ASTRecordWriter::AddUnresolvedSet(const ASTUnresolvedSet &Set) {
6001 Record->push_back(Set.size());
6002 for (ASTUnresolvedSet::const_iterator
6003 I = Set.begin(), E = Set.end(); I != E; ++I) {
6004 AddDeclRef(I.getDecl());
6005 Record->push_back(I.getAccess());
6006 }
6007}
6008
6009// FIXME: Move this out of the main ASTRecordWriter interface.
6010void ASTRecordWriter::AddCXXBaseSpecifier(const CXXBaseSpecifier &Base) {
6011 Record->push_back(Base.isVirtual());
6012 Record->push_back(Base.isBaseOfClass());
6013 Record->push_back(Base.getAccessSpecifierAsWritten());
6014 Record->push_back(Base.getInheritConstructors());
6015 AddTypeSourceInfo(Base.getTypeSourceInfo());
6016 AddSourceRange(Base.getSourceRange());
6017 AddSourceLocation(Base.isPackExpansion()? Base.getEllipsisLoc()
6018 : SourceLocation());
6019}
6020
6021static uint64_t EmitCXXBaseSpecifiers(ASTWriter &W,
6022 ArrayRef<CXXBaseSpecifier> Bases) {
6023 ASTWriter::RecordData Record;
6024 ASTRecordWriter Writer(W, Record);
6025 Writer.push_back(Bases.size());
6026
6027 for (auto &Base : Bases)
6028 Writer.AddCXXBaseSpecifier(Base);
6029
6030 return Writer.Emit(serialization::DECL_CXX_BASE_SPECIFIERS);
6031}
6032
6033// FIXME: Move this out of the main ASTRecordWriter interface.
6034void ASTRecordWriter::AddCXXBaseSpecifiers(ArrayRef<CXXBaseSpecifier> Bases) {
6035 AddOffset(EmitCXXBaseSpecifiers(*Writer, Bases));
6036}
6037
6038static uint64_t
6039EmitCXXCtorInitializers(ASTWriter &W,
6040 ArrayRef<CXXCtorInitializer *> CtorInits) {
6041 ASTWriter::RecordData Record;
6042 ASTRecordWriter Writer(W, Record);
6043 Writer.push_back(CtorInits.size());
6044
6045 for (auto *Init : CtorInits) {
6046 if (Init->isBaseInitializer()) {
6047 Writer.push_back(CTOR_INITIALIZER_BASE);
6048 Writer.AddTypeSourceInfo(Init->getTypeSourceInfo());
6049 Writer.push_back(Init->isBaseVirtual());
6050 } else if (Init->isDelegatingInitializer()) {
6051 Writer.push_back(CTOR_INITIALIZER_DELEGATING);
6052 Writer.AddTypeSourceInfo(Init->getTypeSourceInfo());
6053 } else if (Init->isMemberInitializer()){
6054 Writer.push_back(CTOR_INITIALIZER_MEMBER);
6055 Writer.AddDeclRef(Init->getMember());
6056 } else {
6057 Writer.push_back(CTOR_INITIALIZER_INDIRECT_MEMBER);
6058 Writer.AddDeclRef(Init->getIndirectMember());
6059 }
6060
6061 Writer.AddSourceLocation(Init->getMemberLocation());
6062 Writer.AddStmt(Init->getInit());
6063 Writer.AddSourceLocation(Init->getLParenLoc());
6064 Writer.AddSourceLocation(Init->getRParenLoc());
6065 Writer.push_back(Init->isWritten());
6066 if (Init->isWritten())
6067 Writer.push_back(Init->getSourceOrder());
6068 }
6069
6070 return Writer.Emit(serialization::DECL_CXX_CTOR_INITIALIZERS);
6071}
6072
6073// FIXME: Move this out of the main ASTRecordWriter interface.
6074void ASTRecordWriter::AddCXXCtorInitializers(
6075 ArrayRef<CXXCtorInitializer *> CtorInits) {
6076 AddOffset(EmitCXXCtorInitializers(*Writer, CtorInits));
6077}
6078
6079void ASTRecordWriter::AddCXXDefinitionData(const CXXRecordDecl *D) {
6080 auto &Data = D->data();
6081 Record->push_back(Data.IsLambda);
6082 Record->push_back(Data.UserDeclaredConstructor);
6083 Record->push_back(Data.UserDeclaredSpecialMembers);
6084 Record->push_back(Data.Aggregate);
6085 Record->push_back(Data.PlainOldData);
6086 Record->push_back(Data.Empty);
6087 Record->push_back(Data.Polymorphic);
6088 Record->push_back(Data.Abstract);
6089 Record->push_back(Data.IsStandardLayout);
6090 Record->push_back(Data.IsCXX11StandardLayout);
6091 Record->push_back(Data.HasBasesWithFields);
6092 Record->push_back(Data.HasBasesWithNonStaticDataMembers);
6093 Record->push_back(Data.HasPrivateFields);
6094 Record->push_back(Data.HasProtectedFields);
6095 Record->push_back(Data.HasPublicFields);
6096 Record->push_back(Data.HasMutableFields);
6097 Record->push_back(Data.HasVariantMembers);
6098 Record->push_back(Data.HasOnlyCMembers);
6099 Record->push_back(Data.HasInClassInitializer);
6100 Record->push_back(Data.HasUninitializedReferenceMember);
6101 Record->push_back(Data.HasUninitializedFields);
6102 Record->push_back(Data.HasInheritedConstructor);
6103 Record->push_back(Data.HasInheritedAssignment);
6104 Record->push_back(Data.NeedOverloadResolutionForCopyConstructor);
6105 Record->push_back(Data.NeedOverloadResolutionForMoveConstructor);
6106 Record->push_back(Data.NeedOverloadResolutionForMoveAssignment);
6107 Record->push_back(Data.NeedOverloadResolutionForDestructor);
6108 Record->push_back(Data.DefaultedCopyConstructorIsDeleted);
6109 Record->push_back(Data.DefaultedMoveConstructorIsDeleted);
6110 Record->push_back(Data.DefaultedMoveAssignmentIsDeleted);
6111 Record->push_back(Data.DefaultedDestructorIsDeleted);
6112 Record->push_back(Data.HasTrivialSpecialMembers);
6113 Record->push_back(Data.HasTrivialSpecialMembersForCall);
6114 Record->push_back(Data.DeclaredNonTrivialSpecialMembers);
6115 Record->push_back(Data.DeclaredNonTrivialSpecialMembersForCall);
6116 Record->push_back(Data.HasIrrelevantDestructor);
6117 Record->push_back(Data.HasConstexprNonCopyMoveConstructor);
6118 Record->push_back(Data.HasDefaultedDefaultConstructor);
6119 Record->push_back(Data.DefaultedDefaultConstructorIsConstexpr);
6120 Record->push_back(Data.HasConstexprDefaultConstructor);
6121 Record->push_back(Data.HasNonLiteralTypeFieldsOrBases);
6122 Record->push_back(Data.ComputedVisibleConversions);
6123 Record->push_back(Data.UserProvidedDefaultConstructor);
6124 Record->push_back(Data.DeclaredSpecialMembers);
6125 Record->push_back(Data.ImplicitCopyConstructorCanHaveConstParamForVBase);
6126 Record->push_back(Data.ImplicitCopyConstructorCanHaveConstParamForNonVBase);
6127 Record->push_back(Data.ImplicitCopyAssignmentHasConstParam);
6128 Record->push_back(Data.HasDeclaredCopyConstructorWithConstParam);
6129 Record->push_back(Data.HasDeclaredCopyAssignmentWithConstParam);
6130
6131 // getODRHash will compute the ODRHash if it has not been previously computed.
6132 Record->push_back(D->getODRHash());
6133 bool ModulesDebugInfo = Writer->Context->getLangOpts().ModulesDebugInfo &&
6134 Writer->WritingModule && !D->isDependentType();
6135 Record->push_back(ModulesDebugInfo);
6136 if (ModulesDebugInfo)
6137 Writer->ModularCodegenDecls.push_back(Writer->GetDeclRef(D));
6138
6139 // IsLambda bit is already saved.
6140
6141 Record->push_back(Data.NumBases);
6142 if (Data.NumBases > 0)
6143 AddCXXBaseSpecifiers(Data.bases());
6144
6145 // FIXME: Make VBases lazily computed when needed to avoid storing them.
6146 Record->push_back(Data.NumVBases);
6147 if (Data.NumVBases > 0)
6148 AddCXXBaseSpecifiers(Data.vbases());
6149
6150 AddUnresolvedSet(Data.Conversions.get(*Writer->Context));
6151 AddUnresolvedSet(Data.VisibleConversions.get(*Writer->Context));
6152 // Data.Definition is the owning decl, no need to write it.
6153 AddDeclRef(D->getFirstFriend());
6154
6155 // Add lambda-specific data.
6156 if (Data.IsLambda) {
6157 auto &Lambda = D->getLambdaData();
6158 Record->push_back(Lambda.Dependent);
6159 Record->push_back(Lambda.IsGenericLambda);
6160 Record->push_back(Lambda.CaptureDefault);
6161 Record->push_back(Lambda.NumCaptures);
6162 Record->push_back(Lambda.NumExplicitCaptures);
6163 Record->push_back(Lambda.ManglingNumber);
6164 AddDeclRef(D->getLambdaContextDecl());
6165 AddTypeSourceInfo(Lambda.MethodTyInfo);
6166 for (unsigned I = 0, N = Lambda.NumCaptures; I != N; ++I) {
6167 const LambdaCapture &Capture = Lambda.Captures[I];
6168 AddSourceLocation(Capture.getLocation());
6169 Record->push_back(Capture.isImplicit());
6170 Record->push_back(Capture.getCaptureKind());
6171 switch (Capture.getCaptureKind()) {
6172 case LCK_StarThis:
6173 case LCK_This:
6174 case LCK_VLAType:
6175 break;
6176 case LCK_ByCopy:
6177 case LCK_ByRef:
6178 VarDecl *Var =
6179 Capture.capturesVariable() ? Capture.getCapturedVar() : nullptr;
6180 AddDeclRef(Var);
6181 AddSourceLocation(Capture.isPackExpansion() ? Capture.getEllipsisLoc()
6182 : SourceLocation());
6183 break;
6184 }
6185 }
6186 }
6187}
6188
6189void ASTWriter::ReaderInitialized(ASTReader *Reader) {
6190 assert(Reader && "Cannot remove chain");
6191 assert((!Chain || Chain == Reader) && "Cannot replace chain");
6192 assert(FirstDeclID == NextDeclID &&
6193 FirstTypeID == NextTypeID &&
6194 FirstIdentID == NextIdentID &&
6195 FirstMacroID == NextMacroID &&
6196 FirstSubmoduleID == NextSubmoduleID &&
6197 FirstSelectorID == NextSelectorID &&
6198 "Setting chain after writing has started.");
6199
6200 Chain = Reader;
6201
6202 // Note, this will get called multiple times, once one the reader starts up
6203 // and again each time it's done reading a PCH or module.
6204 FirstDeclID = NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumDecls();
6205 FirstTypeID = NUM_PREDEF_TYPE_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumTypes();
6206 FirstIdentID = NUM_PREDEF_IDENT_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumIdentifiers();
6207 FirstMacroID = NUM_PREDEF_MACRO_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumMacros();
6208 FirstSubmoduleID = NUM_PREDEF_SUBMODULE_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumSubmodules();
6209 FirstSelectorID = NUM_PREDEF_SELECTOR_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumSelectors();
6210 NextDeclID = FirstDeclID;
6211 NextTypeID = FirstTypeID;
6212 NextIdentID = FirstIdentID;
6213 NextMacroID = FirstMacroID;
6214 NextSelectorID = FirstSelectorID;
6215 NextSubmoduleID = FirstSubmoduleID;
6216}
6217
6218void ASTWriter::IdentifierRead(IdentID ID, IdentifierInfo *II) {
6219 // Always keep the highest ID. See \p TypeRead() for more information.
6220 IdentID &StoredID = IdentifierIDs[II];
6221 if (ID > StoredID)
6222 StoredID = ID;
6223}
6224
6225void ASTWriter::MacroRead(serialization::MacroID ID, MacroInfo *MI) {
6226 // Always keep the highest ID. See \p TypeRead() for more information.
6227 MacroID &StoredID = MacroIDs[MI];
6228 if (ID > StoredID)
6229 StoredID = ID;
6230}
6231
6232void ASTWriter::TypeRead(TypeIdx Idx, QualType T) {
6233 // Always take the highest-numbered type index. This copes with an interesting
6234 // case for chained AST writing where we schedule writing the type and then,
6235 // later, deserialize the type from another AST. In this case, we want to
6236 // keep the higher-numbered entry so that we can properly write it out to
6237 // the AST file.
6238 TypeIdx &StoredIdx = TypeIdxs[T];
6239 if (Idx.getIndex() >= StoredIdx.getIndex())
6240 StoredIdx = Idx;
6241}
6242
6243void ASTWriter::SelectorRead(SelectorID ID, Selector S) {
6244 // Always keep the highest ID. See \p TypeRead() for more information.
6245 SelectorID &StoredID = SelectorIDs[S];
6246 if (ID > StoredID)
6247 StoredID = ID;
6248}
6249
6250void ASTWriter::MacroDefinitionRead(serialization::PreprocessedEntityID ID,
6251 MacroDefinitionRecord *MD) {
6252 assert(MacroDefinitions.find(MD) == MacroDefinitions.end());
6253 MacroDefinitions[MD] = ID;
6254}
6255
6256void ASTWriter::ModuleRead(serialization::SubmoduleID ID, Module *Mod) {
6257 assert(SubmoduleIDs.find(Mod) == SubmoduleIDs.end());
6258 SubmoduleIDs[Mod] = ID;
6259}
6260
6261void ASTWriter::CompletedTagDefinition(const TagDecl *D) {
6262 if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords()) return;
6263 assert(D->isCompleteDefinition());
6264 assert(!WritingAST && "Already writing the AST!");
6265 if (auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D)) {
6266 // We are interested when a PCH decl is modified.
6267 if (RD->isFromASTFile()) {
6268 // A forward reference was mutated into a definition. Rewrite it.
6269 // FIXME: This happens during template instantiation, should we
6270 // have created a new definition decl instead ?
6271 assert(isTemplateInstantiation(RD->getTemplateSpecializationKind()) &&
6272 "completed a tag from another module but not by instantiation?");
6273 DeclUpdates[RD].push_back(
6274 DeclUpdate(UPD_CXX_INSTANTIATED_CLASS_DEFINITION));
6275 }
6276 }
6277}
6278
6279static bool isImportedDeclContext(ASTReader *Chain, const Decl *D) {
6280 if (D->isFromASTFile())
6281 return true;
6282
6283 // The predefined __va_list_tag struct is imported if we imported any decls.
6284 // FIXME: This is a gross hack.
6285 return D == D->getASTContext().getVaListTagDecl();
6286}
6287
6288void ASTWriter::AddedVisibleDecl(const DeclContext *DC, const Decl *D) {
6289 if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords()) return;
6290 assert(DC->isLookupContext() &&
6291 "Should not add lookup results to non-lookup contexts!");
6292
6293 // TU is handled elsewhere.
6294 if (isa<TranslationUnitDecl>(DC))
6295 return;
6296
6297 // Namespaces are handled elsewhere, except for template instantiations of
6298 // FunctionTemplateDecls in namespaces. We are interested in cases where the
6299 // local instantiations are added to an imported context. Only happens when
6300 // adding ADL lookup candidates, for example templated friends.
6301 if (isa<NamespaceDecl>(DC) && D->getFriendObjectKind() == Decl::FOK_None &&
6302 !isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D))
6303 return;
6304
6305 // We're only interested in cases where a local declaration is added to an
6306 // imported context.
6307 if (D->isFromASTFile() || !isImportedDeclContext(Chain, cast<Decl>(DC)))
6308 return;
6309
6310 assert(DC == DC->getPrimaryContext() && "added to non-primary context");
6311 assert(!getDefinitiveDeclContext(DC) && "DeclContext not definitive!");
6312 assert(!WritingAST && "Already writing the AST!");
6313 if (UpdatedDeclContexts.insert(DC) && !cast<Decl>(DC)->isFromASTFile()) {
6314 // We're adding a visible declaration to a predefined decl context. Ensure
6315 // that we write out all of its lookup results so we don't get a nasty
6316 // surprise when we try to emit its lookup table.
6317 for (auto *Child : DC->decls())
6318 DeclsToEmitEvenIfUnreferenced.push_back(Child);
6319 }
6320 DeclsToEmitEvenIfUnreferenced.push_back(D);
6321}
6322
6323void ASTWriter::AddedCXXImplicitMember(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, const Decl *D) {
6324 if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords()) return;
6325 assert(D->isImplicit());
6326
6327 // We're only interested in cases where a local declaration is added to an
6328 // imported context.
6329 if (D->isFromASTFile() || !isImportedDeclContext(Chain, RD))
6330 return;
6331
6332 if (!isa<CXXMethodDecl>(D))
6333 return;
6334
6335 // A decl coming from PCH was modified.
6336 assert(RD->isCompleteDefinition());
6337 assert(!WritingAST && "Already writing the AST!");
6338 DeclUpdates[RD].push_back(DeclUpdate(UPD_CXX_ADDED_IMPLICIT_MEMBER, D));
6339}
6340
6341void ASTWriter::ResolvedExceptionSpec(const FunctionDecl *FD) {
6342 if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords()) return;
6343 assert(!DoneWritingDeclsAndTypes && "Already done writing updates!");
6344 if (!Chain) return;
6345 Chain->forEachImportedKeyDecl(FD, [&](const Decl *D) {
6346 // If we don't already know the exception specification for this redecl
6347 // chain, add an update record for it.
6348 if (isUnresolvedExceptionSpec(cast<FunctionDecl>(D)
6349 ->getType()
6350 ->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()
6351 ->getExceptionSpecType()))
6352 DeclUpdates[D].push_back(UPD_CXX_RESOLVED_EXCEPTION_SPEC);
6353 });
6354}

6356void ASTWriter::DeducedReturnType(const FunctionDecl *FD, QualType ReturnType) {
6357 if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords()) return;
6358 assert(!WritingAST && "Already writing the AST!");
6359 if (!Chain) return;
6360 Chain->forEachImportedKeyDecl(FD, [&](const Decl *D) {
6361 DeclUpdates[D].push_back(
6362 DeclUpdate(UPD_CXX_DEDUCED_RETURN_TYPE, ReturnType));
6363 });
6364}

6406void ASTWriter::InstantiationRequested(const ValueDecl *D) {
6407 if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords()) return;
6408 assert(!WritingAST && "Already writing the AST!");
6409 if (!D->isFromASTFile())
6410 return;
6411
6412 // Since the actual instantiation is delayed, this really means that we need
6413 // to update the instantiation location.
6414 SourceLocation POI;
6415 if (auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D))
6416 POI = VD->getPointOfInstantiation();
6417 else
6418 POI = cast<FunctionDecl>(D)->getPointOfInstantiation();
6419 DeclUpdates[D].push_back(DeclUpdate(UPD_CXX_POINT_OF_INSTANTIATION, POI));
6420}

6453void ASTWriter::DeclarationMarkedUsed(const Decl *D) {
6454 if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords()) return;
6455 assert(!WritingAST && "Already writing the AST!");
6456
6457 // If there is *any* declaration of the entity that's not from an AST file,
6458 // we can skip writing the update record. We make sure that isUsed() triggers
6459 // completion of the redeclaration chain of the entity.
6460 for (auto Prev = D->getMostRecentDecl(); Prev; Prev = Prev->getPreviousDecl())
6461 if (IsLocalDecl(Prev))
6462 return;
6463
6464 DeclUpdates[D].push_back(DeclUpdate(UPD_DECL_MARKED_USED));
6465}

6552void OMPClauseWriter::writeClause(OMPClause *C) {
6553 Record.push_back(C->getClauseKind());
6554 Visit(C);
6555 Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getBeginLoc());
6556 Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getEndLoc());
6557}

6562}

6567}

6573 Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getColonLoc());
6574 Record.AddStmt(C->getCondition());
6575 Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getLParenLoc());
6576}

6615void OMPClauseWriter::VisitOMPProcBindClause(OMPProcBindClause *C) {

6634void OMPClauseWriter::VisitOMPOrderedClause(OMPOrderedClause *C) {
6635 Record.push_back(C->getLoopNumIterations().size());
6636 Record.AddStmt(C->getNumForLoops());
6637 for (Expr *NumIter : C->getLoopNumIterations())
6638 Record.AddStmt(NumIter);
6639 for (unsigned I = 0, E = C->getLoopNumIterations().size(); I <E; ++I)
6640 Record.AddStmt(C->getLoopCounter(I));
6641 Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getLParenLoc());
6642}

6861void OMPClauseWriter::VisitOMPMapClause(OMPMapClause *C) {
6862 Record.push_back(C->varlist_size());
6863 Record.push_back(C->getUniqueDeclarationsNum());
6864 Record.push_back(C->getTotalComponentListNum());
6865 Record.push_back(C->getTotalComponentsNum());
6866 Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getLParenLoc());
6867 for (unsigned I = 0; I < OMPMapClause::NumberOfModifiers; ++I) {
6868 Record.push_back(C->getMapTypeModifier(I));
6869 Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getMapTypeModifierLoc(I));
6870 }
6871 Record.AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(C->getMapperQualifierLoc());
6872 Record.AddDeclarationNameInfo(C->getMapperIdInfo());
6873 Record.push_back(C->getMapType());
6874 Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getMapLoc());
6875 Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getColonLoc());
6876 for (auto *E : C->varlists())
6877 Record.AddStmt(E);
6878 for (auto *E : C->mapperlists())
6879 Record.AddStmt(E);
6880 for (auto *D : C->all_decls())
6881 Record.AddDeclRef(D);
6882 for (auto N : C->all_num_lists())
6883 Record.push_back(N);
6884 for (auto N : C->all_lists_sizes())
6885 Record.push_back(N);
6886 for (auto &M : C->all_components()) {
6887 Record.AddStmt(M.getAssociatedExpression());
6888 Record.AddDeclRef(M.getAssociatedDeclaration());
6889 }
6890}
